            "questionText": "Consider a scenario where a homeowner replaces an old wooden countertop with a stainless steel one. It is known that metals generally have higher thermal conductivity than wood, affecting how quickly they exchange heat with the human skin. Given a stainless steel countertop with a thermal conductivity of $!$k_{SS} \\text{ W/m}\\cdot\\text{K}$!$ and an old wooden countertop with a thermal conductivity of $!$k_{wood} \\text{ W/m}\\cdot\\text{K}$!$, calculate the ratio $!$\\frac{k_{SS}}{k_{wood}}$!$. (Note: Please provide the numerical values for $!$k_{SS}$!$ and $!$k_{wood}$!$.)",
